ARBITRAL AWARD 

Date: 20.12.2026
Tribunal: Justice A.K. Rastogi (Presiding), Shri B.L. Sharma, Shri C.P. Singh

FINDINGS
1. Delay in Handover: It is an admitted position that forest clearance was delayed. Site was not unencumbered. Claim 1 allowed at ₹12.50 Cr.
2. Escalation & Extras: Allowed as per CPWD indices and written instructions. Claims 2 and 3 allowed at ₹8.00 Cr and ₹10.50 Cr respectively.
3. Termination: Held illegal. Once the contractor validly suspended work for non-payment, employer cannot terminate for "abandonment".

AWARD
Claimant awarded ₹41.65 Crore + 8.5% interest p.a. from date of invocation.
Counter claim of Respondent rejected except ₹2.15 Cr towards minor LD for rectifiable defects.
Costs of arbitration to be borne by Respondent NHAI.
